Durban - Durban attorney Ravin Singh was among those present at the bail application of the Verulam man accused of raping his 10-year-old stepdaughter. Speaking outside the Verulam Magistrate's Court on Monday, Singh said he represented the victim's family in this matter. "We are here to oversee the interests of the child. Our instructions essentially entail overseeing the bail application relating to the accused, our instructions are to ensure that the application is opposed in light of the serious allegations made against the accused." The 43 year who faces charges of rape and sexual assault, was then taken to a state hospital after he was allegedly assaulted by members of the community, shortly after he was apprehended by a security company. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
